needs - not your household income. <abbr title=\"Disabled Students' Allowances\">DSAs</abbr> are paid on top of your student finance and you don&rsquo;t have to pay them back.</p>\n\n<p>You can get help with the costs of:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>specialist equipment, like computer software</li>\n  <li>non-medical helpers, like a note-taker or reader</li>\n  <li>extra travel costs you have to pay because of your disability</li>\n  <li>other costs, like photocopying </li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p><abbr title=\"Disabled Students' Allowances\">DSAs</abbr> don’t cover disability-related costs you’d have if you weren’t attending a course, or costs that any student might have.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Maximum amounts</h2>\n\n<p>The figures below are the maximum you can get - most students get less than this. </p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Type of student</th>\n      <th>Specialist equipment allowance</th>\n      <th>Non-medical helper allowance</th>\n      <th>General allowance</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Full-time</td>\n      <td>Up to £5,161 for the whole course</td>\n      <td>Up to £20,520 a year</td>\n      <td>Up to £1,724 a year</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Part-time</td>\n      <td>Up to £5,161 for the whole course</td>\n      <td>Up to £15,390 a year</td>\n      <td>Up to £1,293 a year</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Postgraduate students can get a single allowance of up to £10,260.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Part-time students</h2>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re a part-time student the &lsquo;course intensity&rsquo; may affect how much <abbr title=\"Disabled Students' Allowance\">DSA</abbr> you get. Intensity means how long your course takes to complete each year compared to an equivalent full-time course. Your course must:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>last at least 1 year</li>\n  <li>not last more than 4 times as long as the equivalent full-time course </li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If your course starts <strong>before</strong> 1 September 2012 it must not last more than twice as long as the equivalent full-time course.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Your ‘needs assessment’</h2>\n\n<p>Once your eligibility for <abbr title=\"Disabled Students' Allowances\">DSAs</abbr> has been confirmed, Student Finance England will ask you to have a &lsquo;needs assessment&rsquo; to work out what help you need. </p>\n\n<p>You shouldn&rsquo;t book a needs assessment until Student Finance England ask you to. </p>\n\n<p>The assessment is paid for through any <abbr title=\"Disabled Students' Allowances\">DSAs</abbr> entitlement you may have.</p>\n\n<p>After the assessment, you’ll get a report listing equipment and other support you can get for your course.</p>\n\n<h2>How <abbr title=\"Disabled Students' Allowances\">DSAs</abbr> are paid</h2>\n\n<p>Money is paid directly to who provides the service or equipment or into your bank account.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/disabled-students-allowances-dsas/eligibility","slug":"eligibility","order":3,"title":"Eligibility","body":"<p>You can apply for Disabled Students&rsquo; Allowances (<abbr title=\"Disabled Students' Allowances\">DSAs</abbr>) if you have a: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>disability or long-term health condition</li>\n  <li>mental health condition </li>\n  <li>specific learning difficulty like dyslexia or dyspraxia</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You must also:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>be an undergraduate or postgraduate student (including Open University or distance learning)</li>\n  <li>have a condition that affects your ability to study </li>\n  <li>qualify for student finance from Student Finance England</li>\n  <li>be studying on a course that lasts at least a year</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Who isn&rsquo;t eligible</h2>\n\n<p>You can’t get <abbr title=\"Disabled Students' Allowances\">DSAs</abbr> from Student Finance England if you’re:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>an EU student<